<note number="4"> The values of this attribute are defined by reference data, and include values such as "predicted" and "measured".</note>
</ext_description>


<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Probability_distribution_arm  Entity: Parameterized_distribution  
   <express_ref linkend="probability_distribution:arm:Probability_distribution_arm.Parameterized_distribution"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->

<ext_description linkend="Probability_distribution_arm.Parameterized_distribution">
<b>Parameterized_distribution</b> is used to link a named probability distribution to the parameters that define it.
<note number="5">The <b>id</b> and <b>name</b> of this entity are used to discriminate between alternative parameterizations of the same distribution. Alternative parameterizations can be derived from each other.</note>
<note number="6">To calculate a value using a paramaterized_distribution it is necessary to know the general distribution function, the value
of the distribution function parameters, and the specific random variable value for which the probability evaluation is required.
The Probability Distribution module does not define the formula for the distribution function, and it is assumed that this id defined externally, either through reference
information or via a "formula" module. This entity provides the distribution function parameters. The value of the random variable for which the probability
is calculated is provided by <express_ref linkend="probability:arm:Probability_arm.Parameter.parameter_role"/>.</note>
</ext_description>


